UID:10001827-1776180600-1776187800@www.culturelink.ca
SUMMARY:Youth Connect Hub
DESCRIPTION:A safe and welcoming space for youth to connect\, relax\, and have fun. Enjoy group games\, creative activities\, food sessions\, and conversations that support emotional well-being and confidence. \nFor Newcomer Youth: 13 to 24 Years Old\nBiweekly Sessions from February 3rd to April 14th \nPriority will be given to Permanent residents and Convention Refugees. All newcomers are welcome! \nTo Register\, contact Kehinde at KOyinloye@culturelink.ca or or Chelsea at CRanger@culturelink.ca\, or call (437) 288-9505 \nOr you can fill in the form below: \n﻿
URL:https://www.culturelink.ca/event/youth-connect-hub/2026-04-14/
LOCATION:CultureLink Children & Youth Centre\, 3535 Dundas Street West\, Toronto\, Ontario\, Canada
CATEGORIES:Newcomer Youth Success,Youth
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.culturelink.ca/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Youth-Wellness-Community-CultureLink-Icon.jpg
END:VEVENT
