DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260417T143000
DTSTAMP:20260404T230819
CREATED:20260327T200706Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260327T201237Z
UID:10001905-1776430800-1776436200@www.culturelink.ca
SUMMARY:Mentoring & Networking with Bobrick
DESCRIPTION:Explore the possibilities of a manufacturing career at Bobrick. \n\nTour the Bobrick facilities in Scarborough\nObserve a typical manufacturing operation running\nGet insights into roles available in the industry\n\nParticipants must be: \n\nInternational trained professionals\nPermanent Residents or Convention Refugees\nAt least 19 years old\nJob-ready English proficiency level\n\nThere is limited parking available on-site. Please allow extra time for arrival\, and take advantage of free/paid street parking available throughout the neighbourhood. \nTo participate\, fill in the Registration Form. \nFor more information\, contact Rubina at rafsar@culturelink.ca or Victor at vgomes@culturelink.ca.
URL:https://www.culturelink.ca/event/mentoring-networking-with-bobrick-2026-04-17/
LOCATION:Bobrick\, 45 Rolark Drive\, Scarborough\, Ontario\, M1R3B1\, Canada
CATEGORIES:Adults
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.culturelink.ca/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Adults-Mentorship-and-Networking-CultureLink-Icon.jpg
END:VEVENT
